Text: This week has been the most productive for myself in terms of learning and understanding the project.
We took the advice of dropping the Javascript and just using python to connect R with Cassandra which certainly seems better.
Starting with Javascipt was interesting though and a good learning experience.
The group also took the advice of focusing on users and looking at what information they would want to see.
We are working on a focus group to understand this better, and Rodney has now sent some queries he would like to have answers to as the admin / product owner.
There was some confusion regarding the NDA Rodney sent out early in the week.
He's a bit eccentric and after reading it i didn't feel comfortable signing it given the circumstances.
He seemed happy enough with that in the reply.
I probably could have handled that better and i hope that didn't cause any problems.
Roro and I had an interesting meeting with Rodney and his lead developer Yann.
They discussed the project details between each other and decided that we should direct our efforts to modeling rather than implementation.
Yann outlined the process of reverse engineering specific questions into attributes and translating them back into reports.
Roro and I are focusing on this and have built a pretty good series of models in a Lucid chart collaboration, Riri is leading the focus group.
Because Roro has written a lot of working code already and it fits our learning goals better, we're thinkingÂ that we'llÂ continue with the initial scope of the project.
I think we should give a little extra attention to the modeling part to ensure Rodney is happy with the outcome, but i'm yet to discuss this with the team.
Our goals this week are to get some working tables in Cassandra that answer some queries and get the focus group completed.
